    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/1773½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Counselor for the Department of State</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lansing</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="47" xml:id="d349fn1">This paper is undated; it bears the
                        following notation in Lansing’s hand: “May 12/15 RL.”</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1915-05-12">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: I enclose a draft of note to
                    Germany drawn by the President.<note n="48" xml:id="d349fn2">See footnote 43,
                            <ref target="#pg_392">p. 392</ref>.</note> He asks for our suggestions.
                    I wish you would prepare <hi rend="underline">at once</hi> a draft embodying
                    yours—I will submit mine in a letter to accompany the draft when sent back to
                    the President. I shall be detained here for a while but will be down before your
                    draft is completed.</p>
                <p>Yours</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
